laboratory_examinations.findings: Additional chromosomal material within the long arm of chromosome 16.

Fluorescence in situ hybridization showed two regions of hybridization indicating the duplication on chromosome 16q13 and revealed one hybridization signal per 16q at D16S512, confirming the region is not involved in the duplication.
Densitometric analysis indicated D16S400, D16S3137, D16S3032, and D16S408 were included in the duplication, whereas D16S419 and D16S421 were not.
